      passage: `Outi Tervo and team studied the effect of human-caused noise on narwhals (<i>Monodon monoceros</i>), arctic marine mammals that are sensitive to acoustic changes. Hypothesizing that elevated sound levels affect foraging, Tervo's team compared narwhal diving behaviors in natural sound conditions with those in two human-caused exposure conditions—ship sounds and ship sounds coupled with sonic pulses. Both exposure conditions resulted in significant decreases in the number and target depth of deep dives (associated with foraging) relative to natural conditions. However, differences between diving behaviors in the two exposure types were negligible, a finding that could be attributed to the fact that ______`,
